http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Meeting-on-e-governance-today/article14026334.ece

The Department of Information Technology, Electronics and Communication, in association with the Elets Technomedia, is conducting a symposium on ‘e-governance’ at Hotel Grand Ridge, Tirupati on Friday.Academicians, industry representatives, thought leaders, practitioners, secretaries and government functionaries will participate in the event to showcase the e-governance initiatives, including e-pragathi. Great Lakes Institute of Management founder and JL Kellogg distinguished Professor Bala V. Balachandran and Delhi Dialogue Commission Vice-Chairman Ashish Khetan will share their ideas.IT Minister Palle Raghunatha Reddy, Telecom Secretary Rakesh Garg will participate in the inaugural.